            "abstractNote": "Tropical karst environments are critically sensitive and thus require careful management. For over fourcenturiesfarmerson the Philippineislandof Bohol have adapteda karstenvironmentto a sustainablecarabao/wetrice agriculturalsystem. Such time-honoredadaptationsto these karsticconditionsformanimportantexampleof effective and viable karst occupance. Through conservative strategiesthe populationhasmaintainedproductionwithout widespread incorporation of 'Green Revolution' technologies prescribed by development agencies. However, pressures for 'modern' economic development threatenthe fragilekarstenvironment.If developmentis to improveratherthandegradelandscapes,the productivepotentials of the existing culturaland physicalvariablesmust be identified and analysed, including hydrology, regional demographics, cultivars, and traditional agrarianpractice and structure.These variablesand their interrelationsprovide the foundations of a productive karst agroecosystem whichplannersshouldintegrateinto developmentstrategies before imposingstructural/environmentaclhanges.",
